---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { meta } from "../lib/data.js";
const m = meta();
---
<Base title="About — SUCCURRO">
  <h1>About SUCCURRO</h1>
  <p>
    <em>Succurro</em> (Latin): to run to the aid of, to help. This is a curated,
    source-anchored dataset and directory of help and support services across the
    United States, resolved to the city and town level.
  </p>
  <p>
    Every record cites its source and carries a verification date. Records that
    go stale are flagged; safety-critical listings are suppressed rather than
    shown stale. Confidential shelter locations are never published — only
    hotline and intake contacts. Meeting listings carry venue and schedule facts
    only, respecting the anonymity traditions of the fellowships they describe.
  </p>
  <p>
    Data comes from federal open data (SAMHSA, HRSA, VA, HUD, USDA, ACF, DOJ),
    open community feeds (the BMLT and Meeting Guide ecosystems), and facts-only
    curation of public directories — {m.counts.sources} sources in all, listed in
    the <a href="https://github.com/KaraZajac/SUCCURRO/blob/master/docs/sources.md">source registry</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The dataset is CC BY-NC 4.0 and lives on
    <a href="https://github.com/KaraZajac/SUCCURRO">GitHub</a>. Corrections and
    takedown requests are honored without argument — open an issue or email
    <a href="mailto:kara@soulstone.org">kara@soulstone.org</a>. If you run a
    service listed here and want it updated or removed, that is your call, not
    ours.
  </p>
  <p>
    Not affiliated with any listed organization. In an emergency call 911; in a
    mental-health crisis call or text 988.
  </p>
</Base>
